{
  "stem": "21626.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But I'll come to the man later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "He's not really a part of this scene, because my parents didn't know anything about him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "By then, he was back in England looking for homes and, and families to, to be able to save as many endangered children as possible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That was May-- as I said, it was end of May 1939 when we learned we could come.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And after that, of course, there was frantic activity to get us ready.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I remember Mother buying materials and taking us to the dressmaker and having a completely new wardrobe made for both of us to send us to England.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And everything was made to fit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Nothing allowed for growth, because the only way they could-- our parents could sustain themselves, could sustain their optimism, was by saying to themselves and to us, you will be back within a year.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You'll see.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Had we entertained the possibility that we might be separated for years, or forever as was in our case, they probably would not have had the strength to do it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When the moment finally came for us to leave, which was at the end of June, I had said goodbye to my school and my friends.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "This bosom pal of mine, Marta, is more than worth her mention.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "She was my shadow for many years and a real good friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And you know, my greatest passion in those early childhood days were cats.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I used to collect everybody's cats off the streets, thinking they must be lost or hungry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they weren't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I had one cat who kept producing kittens.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And her name was Julius.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "When we got her, we thought she was a male.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
